context: Alaska has <a2_0><b6_0><b7_0>few<b7_0/><b6_0/><a2_0/> road connections compared to the rest of the U.S. The state's road system covers a relatively small area of the state, linking the central population centers and the Alaska Highway, the principal route out of the state through Canada. The state capital, <a0_0><b3_0>Juneau, is not accessible by road<b3_0/><a0_0/>, only a car ferry, which has spurred several debates over the decades about moving the capital to a city on the road system, or building a road connection from Haines. <b4_0><b5_0>The <a1_0>western part<b5_0/><b4_0/><a1_0/> of Alaska has no road system connecting the communities with the rest of Alaska.
